The paper introduces a new structural graph parameter and uses it to establish a lower bound on the size of non-deterministic read-once branching programs (NROBPs). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests that it may also belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GT), and logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-categories.
